                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 26.) I was watching the prisoner for half an hour, and saw him feeling several pockets—I afterwards saw him put his hand into the prosecutor's pocket, and take this handkerchief from it—I took him into custody, and took it from his hand—at the station I found these two other handkerchiefs on him, one in his trowsers' pocket, and the other in his coat pocket—they are silk handkerchiefs, and of different patterns—from inquiries I have made I believe one of them is his own, and I believe he bears a good character.</p>
